history.content: Please contact the IEOR department, this is EECS 101.

I'm not entirely sure how this came to happen, but at the time of my phase 1 a while ago IEOR 171 and IEOR 172's lecture times did not conflict and so I was able to enroll in them both as well as another CS class with no issues. However, I just rechecked my schedule as I knew that some of the discussions were still TBA (one class' still is), and unfortunately found out that now the lecture times for the two IEOR classes conflict once a week. Given that IEOR 172 is essentially a math/stat class, I'm thinking I could learn the material just fine not attending lecture and simply using lecture notes or whatever is possible. Could anyone confirm whether attendance is required for 172 lectures, and/or if the fact that those two lectures conflict will be an issue in any other way?

Thanks!
history.subject: Conflict in classes already enrolled in
